Assistant: Absolutely! Here are some practical examples to help you out:

**Install Radix Themes**:

```yaml
npm install @radix-ui/themes
```

This snippet shows you how to install radix themes, which is an important aspect of getting started with radix themes.

**Import the CSS file**:

```yaml
import "@radix-ui/themes/styles.css";
```

This snippet shows you how to import the css file, which is an important aspect of getting started with radix themes.

**Add the Theme component**:

```yaml
import { Theme } from "@radix-ui/themes";

export default function () {
	return (
		<html>
			<body>
				<Theme>
					<MyApp />
				</Theme>
			</body>
		</html>
	);
}
```

This snippet shows you how to add the theme component, which is an important aspect of getting started with radix themes.

**Start building**:

```yaml
import { Flex, Text, Button } from "@radix-ui/themes";

export default function MyApp() {
	return (
		<Flex direction="column" gap="2">
			<Text>Hello from Radix Themes :)</Text>
			<Button>Let's go</Button>
		</Flex>
	);
}
```

This snippet shows you how to start building, which is an important aspect of getting started with radix themes.

**Basic configuration**:

```yaml
<Theme accentColor="crimson" grayColor="sand" radius="large" scaling="95%">
	<MyApp />
</Theme>
```

This snippet shows you how to basic configuration, which is an important aspect of getting started with radix themes.

**Using the theme panel**:

```yaml
import { Theme, ThemePanel } from "@radix-ui/themes";

export default function () {
	return (
		<Theme>
			<MyApp />
			<ThemePanel />
		</Theme>
	);
}
```

This snippet shows you how to using the theme panel, which is an important aspect of getting started with radix themes.

